    <title type="html"><![CDATA[How to upload files when testing using Selenium Webdriver]]></title>
    <link href="http://navaneeth.github.com/blog/2013/02/20/how-to-upload-files-when-testing-using-selenium-webdriver/"/>
    <updated>2013-02-20T15:42:00+05:30</updated>
    <id>http://navaneeth.github.com/blog/2013/02/20/how-to-upload-files-when-testing-using-selenium-webdriver</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>You can use the following code to set a file path to the file upload control.</p>

<p><code>java
WebElement file = driver.findElement(By.id("control_id"));
file.sendKeys("/full/path/to/file");
</code></p>

<p>You need to pass full path to the <code>sendKeys()</code> for it to work. Otherwise <code>sendKeys()</code> fails silently.</p>
